\p{\strong{passport.gay} — your brain is your passport. Brainwave entropy during AI sessions as decentralized identity. No iris scans. No stored biometrics. Continuous authentication. \code{did:gay:*} on Aptos.}

\subtree{\title{Problem: iris scanning is already banned}
\p{WorldID requires proprietary Orb hardware ($5K+), stores biometric iris templates, and has been ordered to delete data across multiple continents. Thailand demanded deletion of 1.2M+ iris scans. Kenya barred all biometric collection. GDPR investigations in Germany, Spain, Portugal. Centralized infrastructure. Binary classification.}
}

\subtree{\title{Three pillars of identity}
\p{Browser fingerprints are passive (~70 bits). Brainwaves are biological (82 bits). Interaction entropy is behavioral (~25 bits). passport.gay fuses all three into a single 11-dimensional Gärdenfors conceptual space.}
\table{
  \tr{\th{Pillar} \th{Trit} \th{Bits} \th{Source}}
  \tr{\td{Browser Fingerprint (FP)} \td{#{-1} verify} \td{~70} \td{Canvas, WebGL, UA, fonts — passively extracted}}
  \tr{\td{Proof of Brain (EEG)} \td{#{0} coordinate} \td{82} \td{Shannon entropy of band powers during LLM conversation — requires consent + device}}
  \tr{\td{Interaction Entropy (IX)} \td{#{+1} generate} \td{~25} \td{Keystroke dynamics + conversation topology + sonic identity}}
}
\p{Conservation: #{(-1) + 0 + (+1) = 0}. No single pillar is sufficient alone.}
}

\subtree{\title{Pipeline}
\p{EEG (8-channel, 250 Hz via OpenBCI Cyton [[bcf-0010]]) → FFT (5 bands: #{δ, θ, α, β, γ}) → Shannon entropy #{H(X)} → GF(3) trit assignment → \code{did:gay} on-chain identity.}
\p{This is exactly the bci.blue afferent sieve ([[bcf-0019]]) applied to identity rather than decode. The pipeline reuses Stages 1--3 of the T-55 stack ([[horse-0002]], [[horse-0003]], [[horse-0004]]).}
}

\subtree{\title{Advantages over WorldID}
\ul{
  \li{\strong{Continuous auth}: every session re-proves identity, not one-time enrollment.}
  \li{\strong{Template revocability}: change cognitive task, get a new template. Iris is fixed.}
  \li{\strong{Coercion detection}: stress measurably alters EEG patterns. Iris scans cannot detect duress.}
  \li{\strong{No stored biometrics}: entropy computed in real-time, only SHA-256 commitment on-chain. GDPR-native.}
  \li{\strong{GF(3) triadic identity}: not binary human/bot — three cognitive states: Generator (+1), Ergodic (0), Validator (-1).}
  \li{\strong{Diffusion model defense}: #{1/f} spectral analysis detects synthetic EEG. Real brains have pink noise.}
}
}

\subtree{\title{Gärdenfors conceptual spaces}
\p{Identity lives in a geometric space of quality dimensions. Browser fingerprints give ~70 bits. Brainwaves give 82 bits. Together: an 11-dimensional conceptual space where GF(3) prototypes define a Voronoi tessellation. \strong{Criterion P} (Gärdenfors): a natural property is a convex region in a conceptual space. Three prototypes yield three convex cells — the simplest non-trivial categorization supporting a conservation law.}
}

